  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "TracIn for generative models TracIn has also been used outside of supervised settings.",
    "For example, Kong & Chaudhuri (2021) apply TracIn to unsupervised learning, in particular density estimation; they propose variational autoencoder TracIn (VAE-TracIn), which quantifies the TracIn influence in -VAEs (Higgins et al., 2017).",
    "Moreover, Thimonier et al.'s (2022) TracIn anomaly detector (TracInAD) functionally estimates the distribution of influence estimates-using either TracInCP or VAE-TracIn.",
    "TracInAD then marks as anomalous any test instance in the tail of this \"influence distribution\".",
    "Note also that TracIn can be applied to any iterative, gradient-based model, including those that are non-parametric."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, Kong & Chaudhuri (2021) apply TracIn to unsupervised learning, in particular density estimation; they propose variational autoencoder TracIn (VAE-TracIn), which quantifies the TracIn influence in -VAEs (Higgins et al., 2017).",
    "Moreover, Thimonier et al.'s (2022) TracIn anomaly detector (TracInAD) functionally estimates the distribution of influence estimates-using either TracInCP or VAE-TracIn."
